# KPI Cards Styling Rule

## No Colored Left Borders on KPI Cards

All KPI (Key Performance Indicator) cards must **NOT** have colored left borders. This includes:

### ❌ Forbidden Patterns:
```tsx
// DON'T use colored left borders
<Card className="border-l-4 border-l-orange-500">
<Card className="border-l-4 border-l-green-500">
<Card className="border-l-4 border-l-red-500">
<Card className="border-l-4 border-l-blue-500">
<Card className="border-l-4 border-l-purple-500">
```

### ✅ Correct Patterns:
```tsx
// DO use clean cards without colored left borders
<Card className="hover:shadow-lg transition-all duration-300 hover:-translate-y-1">
<Card className="hover:shadow-md transition-shadow">
<Card className="border border-border">
```

### Implementation Guidelines:

1. **Remove any `border-l-4 border-l-{color}-{shade}` classes** from KPI cards
2. **Use subtle hover effects** instead of colored borders for visual hierarchy
3. **Maintain consistent spacing and shadows** for card distinction
4. **Use icons and typography** to differentiate card types rather than colored borders

### Examples from Codebase:
- [src/app/admin/dashboard/page.tsx](mdc:src/app/admin/dashboard/page.tsx) - Admin dashboard KPI cards
- [src/app/client/dashboard/page.tsx](mdc:src/app/client/dashboard/page.tsx) - Client dashboard KPI cards

### Visual Hierarchy Alternatives:
- Use **icon colors** to indicate card type
- Apply **hover animations** (translate, shadow changes)
- Use **typography weight** and **spacing** for emphasis
- Implement **gradient backgrounds** sparingly for special cards

This rule ensures a clean, modern design without distracting colored left borders on KPI cards.